======================================================================
WHY SEMANTIC ROUTING WINS
======================================================================

Semantic Routing has lower Total Expected Cost because:
  1. Much lower latency: 1.000ms vs 14.901ms
  2. Fewer overpredictions: 314 vs 607
  3. Better balance: 52.8% low accuracy vs 8.9%

SLM's asymmetric loss training made it extremely conservative,
over-predicting risk to avoid missing high-risk cases.
This wastes resources on low/mid queries, increasing expected cost.

Semantic routing achieves a better cost-benefit balance.
